+## Operational Note
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The strategist launched the explorer through
+  `bin/launch-role.sh`, but the runtime only produced a stalled draft and never
+  wrote the required sentinel. This completed report therefore finishes the
+  exploration directly from the frozen local record, matching the Step-2
+  precedent that operational launcher issues do not by themselves block the
+  mathematical step.
+
+## Transformation Taxonomy
+
+### A. True Exact Symmetries
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The relevant exact-symmetry tier is intentionally minimal for
+  this step:
+  only exact Navier-Stokes symmetries applied to the whole closed packet
+  realization that preserve the same internal five-role interaction ledger and
+  are then read back on the same frozen packet sheet.
+- `[INFERRED]` In concrete Step-3 terms, a true symmetry may move or re-express
+  the same exact packet realization, but it may not change:
+  the role set
+  `(A,B,C,D,E)`,
+  the one-bridge packet object,
+  the mandatory conjugate completion rule,
+  the shared five-channel core,
+  or the predeclared thresholds and activation window.
+- `[INFERRED]` This belongs in the symmetry class because these moves do not
+  redefine the object; they leave the same exact packet and the same
+  interaction ledger in place and only realize it in a symmetry-related frame.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The local chain requires invariance under this first class but
+  does not require invariance under every representation move. Sources:
+  `CHAIN.md`,
+  `judgments/chain-01.md`,
+  `decision-005.md`.
+
+### B. Fixed Canonicalization Choices
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` One conjugate-representative convention belongs here.
+  Conjugate completion is mandatory for real-valuedness, but the packet's
+  primary identity is still the role-labeled helical packet rather than the
+  choice of explicit mirror representative. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/conjugate-completion-is-mandatory-canonicalization-not-primary-packet-identity.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` One helical basis convention belongs here.
+  The attack memo explicitly says basis dependence should often be handled by
+  canonicalization rather than by killing the object. Sources:
+  `planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md`,
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` One role-label ordering belongs here.
+  Step 1 already treats relabeling order as cosmetic once the role ledger is
+  frozen. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library-inbox/step-001-exploration-002-packet-language-memo.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` One amplitude normalization anchor belongs here.
+  Step 1 and Step 2 both require one fixed normalization anchor before later
+  comparisons can be honest. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/helical-signs-amplitude-normalization-and-phase-anchor-belong-to-the-frozen-packet-sheet.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` One phase anchor or equivalent gauge belongs here.
+  Phase sensitivity is load-bearing, but the branch treats the anchor as part
+  of the frozen packet sheet rather than a theorem invariant. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/helical-signs-amplitude-normalization-and-phase-anchor-belong-to-the-frozen-packet-sheet.md`.
+- `[INFERRED]` Sign-sheet bookkeeping belongs here only in the weak sense that
+  later computations must be read on one frozen declared sign sheet.
+  The existence of a sign sheet is frozen policy; changing which sign sheet is
+  used is not canonicalization. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library/factual/tao-circuit-feature-ledger/tao-likeness-requires-a-five-part-canonicalization-screen.md`.
+
+### C. Substantive Model Changes
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Packet regrouping is substantive, not cosmetic. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/packet-audits-must-separate-true-symmetries-canonicalization-and-substantive-model-changes.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Switching support semantics among single modes, conjugate pairs,
+  and packet-level objects is substantive. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/support-means-a-role-labeled-helical-packet-with-mandatory-conjugate-completion.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Treating conjugate completion as optional is substantive.
+  Real-valuedness forces it, so dropping it changes the object rather than the
+  presentation. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/conjugate-completion-is-mandatory-canonicalization-not-primary-packet-identity.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Changing the helical sign sheet after the fact is substantive.
+  Sign data is part of the frozen packet sheet and part of the exact mismatch
+  being tested. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/helical-signs-amplitude-normalization-and-phase-anchor-belong-to-the-frozen-packet-sheet.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Changing phase bookkeeping after the anchor is frozen is
+  substantive. Sources:
+  `steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`,
+  `planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Retuning thresholds or the finite time window after seeing
+  outcomes is substantive and often fatal.
+  The chain and attack packet both treat this as threshold gerrymandering.
+  Sources:
+  `CHAIN.md`,
+  `planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md`,
+  `library/factual/navier-stokes/packet-audits-must-separate-true-symmetries-canonicalization-and-substantive-model-changes.md`.
+- `[INFERRED]` Changing the spectator partition is substantive.
+  The leakage candidate uses a frozen partition into
+  `mirror`,
+  `companion`,
+  `feedback`,
+  and
+  `cross`;
+  changing that partition would change the object being measured. Sources:
+  `steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`,
+  `library-inbox/step-002-exploration-002-interaction-templates-and-gates.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Importing Tao's averaged freedoms or averaged coordinates by
+  hand is substantive and mission-fatal when used to rescue a candidate.
+  Sources:
+  `CHAIN.md`,
+  `planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md`,
+  `library/factual/tao-circuit-feature-ledger/destroyed-by-averaging-means-loss-under-averaged-circuit-freedoms-not-under-canonical-relabeling.md`.
